          en: "The float test assesses soup body: when garnishes (croutons, herbs, vegetable dice) are added, they should float briefly then slowly sink as soup permeates them, indicating proper viscosity. If garnishes sink immediately, soup is too thin; if they sit permanently on top, it's too thick. This visual cue helps chefs judge consistency without measuring instruments—experience-based technique for achieving ideal texture.",
